- F-13: prompt()/prompt() payment entry replaced by an in-page modal
  (amount, date picker, live allocation preview via the shared
  waterfall, review-before-commit). Early-payoff/adjust/reminder
  prompts remain — noted as UX backlog, they are numeric/confirm inputs.
- F-02: allocation routed through Calculations.allocateScheduledPayment
  with the interest cap enforced at allocation time (including the
  second-half overpayment branch); partial payments now mark the entry
  'partial' with a per-component paid_breakdown and only 'paid' once
  dues are met; the first-half overpayment interest recalculation now
  propagates into remaining schedule entries and the loan's
  monthly_payment.
- F-06: markAsDefaulted and early payoff recalculate derived totals;
  late-penalty income tracked in totalPenaltiesEarned.
- F-07/F-16: every residual hardcoded rate (12%, 30%, 10%, R60/50/45)
  now reads Calculations.RATES; getStockvelAdminFee delegates to the
  shared rule; schedule start-year via resolveScheduleStartYear.
- F-09: payment/early-payoff/adjustment logs write to the canonical
  AppState.transactions; dual reads consolidated (normalizer merges
  legacy data at load) with an id-dedupe in the adjustment timeline.
- F-04: client-controlled strings escaped in rendered markup; F-17:
  27 verbose logs gated behind DEBUG.

Transforms preserved for audit: tools/transform-active-loans{,-2}.mjs
